    {
      "para_id": "p3",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Response to the European Commission Consultation on the Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 3,
      "text": "NHO Service and Trade (NHO SH) is one of the largest national federations within the Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise (NHO), representing more than 7,000 companies across a wide range of service sectors and retail/trade. Our members include firms in retail, cleaning, staffing, security, facility management and other knowledge- and labour-intensive industries.",
      "char_len": 366,
      "chunk_word_count": 53,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.939873417721519,
        "digit": 0.012658227848101266,
        "non_space": 0.8633879781420765
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9549050632911393,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p4",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Response to the European Commission Consultation on the Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 4,
      "text": "NHO SH works to promote fair competition, responsible business practices and an innovation-friendly regulatory framework in Norway and the European Economic Area. We actively engage in EU policy development to ensure that European regulations support both consumer protection and sustainable business growth.",
      "char_len": 308,
      "chunk_word_count": 42,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9850187265917603,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8668831168831169
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8970973782771536,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p5",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "General remarks"
      ],
      "ordinal": 5,
      "text": "We welcome the European Commission's initiative to modernise EU consumer protection law through the proposed Digital Fairness Act (DFA). The goal of ensuring a transparent and fair digital environment is both timely and important. However, new rules must be carefully designed to balance consumer protection with innovation, competition and the freedom to conduct business.",
      "char_len": 373,
      "chunk_word_count": 54,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.975,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8579088471849866
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.98125,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p6",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "General remarks"
      ],
      "ordinal": 6,
      "text": "We support the overall ambition of the DFA to address manipulative design practices and to ensure a level playing field in digital markets. Nevertheless, we wish to highlight two specific points that we consider essential to safeguard innovation and fair competition.",
      "char_len": 267,
      "chunk_word_count": 41,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.986784140969163,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.850187265917603
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8831436612824279,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "General remarks"
      ],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "Reference is also made to Business Europe's response to the proposals in question. We share the views of Business Europe. In this respect we would like to emphasize two parts of the proposal.",
      "char_len": 191,
      "chunk_word_count": 33,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9748427672955975,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8324607329842932
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7519654088050315,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "We urge the Commission not to introduce the proposed mandatory obligations for price transparency or disclosure of pricing structures beyond what is already required under",
      "char_len": 171,
      "chunk_word_count": 25,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 1.0,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8596491228070176
      },
