    },
    {
      "para_id": "p11",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 11,
      "text": "Risk of reduced competition and innovation Full or mandatory disclosure of pricing mechanisms may unintentionally facilitate price alignment or coordination between competitors, especially in markets with few large actors. Over-transparency can lead to price homogenization rather than fairer outcomes.",
      "char_len": 302,
      "chunk_word_count": 39,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9848484848484849,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8741721854304636
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8511363636363637,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p12",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 12,
      "text": "Harm to SMEs and niche providers Smaller companies often rely on flexible or innovative pricing strategies to compete. Public disclosure of pricing models could erode their competitive edge, making digital markets less diverse and dynamic.",
      "char_len": 239,
      "chunk_word_count": 35,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9853658536585366,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8577405857740585
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7904132791327914,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p13",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 13,
      "text": "Existing safeguards are sufficient EU consumer legislation already ensures that prices must be clearly and unambiguously presented before purchase. Extending these rules to cover internal pricing logic or algorithmic price formation would add administrative burden without tangible consumer benefit.",
      "char_len": 299,
      "chunk_word_count": 39,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9923371647509579,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8729096989966555
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8567528735632184,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p14",
      "section_id": "s5",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Recommendation"
      ],
      "ordinal": 14,
      "text": "The DFA should focus on fairness and clarity in how prices are presented to consumers, not on disclosing how they are set. Innovation in pricing models is a legitimate and important part of competition.",
      "char_len": 202,
      "chunk_word_count": 34,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9822485207100592,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8366336633663366
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7727975016436556,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p15",
      "section_id": "s6",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "2. Ensure fair and transparent digital advertising markets"
      ],
      "ordinal": 15,
      "text": "We support stronger regulation of online advertising systems, in particular auction-based models (real-time bidding) that are today dominated by a few large technology platforms. These systems pose both competition and consumer-protection challenges.",
      "char_len": 250,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9634703196347032,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.876
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.728158295281583,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p16",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 16,
      "text": "Market concentration and lack of transparency The current ad-tech ecosystem is largely controlled by vertically integrated platforms that own the infrastructure for both buying and selling ad space. This dual role distorts competition and limits market access for smaller players.",
      "char_len": 280,
      "chunk_word_count": 40,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9875518672199171,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8607142857142858
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8684416781927156,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p17",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 17,
      "text": "Consumer manipulation and privacy risks Real-time bidding relies on extensive behavioural profiling, often incompatible with",
      "char_len": 124,
      "chunk_word_count": 15,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9818181818181818,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8870967741935484
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.48219696969696973,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p18",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 18,
      "text": "data minimisation and fairness principles under the GDPR and the Digital Services Act (DSA). Consumers rarely understand the scale or implications of these data exchanges.",
      "char_len": 171,
      "chunk_word_count": 25,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9727891156462585,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8596491228070176
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.628202947845805,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
