      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p19",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Our opinion:"
      ],
      "ordinal": 19,
      "text": "Need for interoperability and algorithmic accountability The DFA should complement the DSA and the Digital Markets Act (DMA) by promoting interoperability between ad-tech systems and requiring greater transparency in algorithmic decision-making processes.",
      "char_len": 255,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9776785714285714,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8784313725490196
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7388144841269841,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p20",
      "section_id": "s5",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Recommendation"
      ],
      "ordinal": 20,
      "text": "The EU should establish clear rules to prevent conflicts of interest in digital advertising, ensure transparency in bidding processes, and enable fair competition among advertisers, media and intermediaries.",
      "char_len": 207,
      "chunk_word_count": 28,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9777777777777777,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8695652173913043
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6777777777777778,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s7",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Concluding remarks"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "The Digital Fairness Act offers an opportunity to strengthen trust and accountability in digital markets. However, it should avoid over-regulation that could suppress legitimate innovation or impose disproportionate costs on smaller businesses.",
      "char_len": 244,
      "chunk_word_count": 32,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9812206572769953,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8729508196721312
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.741471048513302,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s7",
      "section_path": [
        "1. Avoid mandatory price transparency obligations",
        "Concluding remarks"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "A well-balanced approach will protect consumers, promote competition and ensure that Europe remains a global leader in digital fairness and responsible innovation.",
      "char_len": 163,
      "chunk_word_count": 22,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9788732394366197,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8711656441717791
